<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900709-0011</DOCNO><DOCID>900709-0011.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Exploration Co. of Louisiana:   Purchase of Further Interest   In Cox Field Area Is Slated</HL><DATE>07/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C18</SO><CO>   XCOL</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Exploration Co. of Louisiana Inc., Lafayette, La., said itagreed to buy additional working interest in the Berry R. CoxField area in south Texas for $40 million, a purchase thatwill make it the field's operator.   The company said the area, still in the early developmentstage, has nine producing wells and proven reserves ofapproximately 200 billion cubic feet of gas. The workinginterests in the producing wells vary from 28% to 49% andinclude proven reserves of about 60 billion cubic feet.</LP><TEXT>   To pay for the acquisition, Exploration said it wouldbegin a rights issue of 600,000 units, each comprising oneshare of preferred stock and 10 warrants. The rights issue isexpected to raise about $50 million, the balance of whichwill be used to reduce bank debt and provide additionalworking capital.   Exploration Co. is an oil and gas exploration andproduction company.</TEXT></DOC>